Title: The Unlikely Sports Enthusiast
Pathologist Neil, who lived next door to the protagonist, was known for his fascination with football (or soccer) despite being in the medical field. His love for the game was evident in his neatly organized sports memorabilia collection, which adorned the walls of his living room.
One day, while walking by Neil’s house, the protagonist stumbled upon him watching an intense match between two top-tier teams. Neil enthusiastically shouted at the screen as if he were part of the crowd, much to the amusement of those around him. It became clear that this was not just any ordinary interest;
